{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_bullock_ver01/data/sn82016181/00516999615/1937121401/1519.xml":{"full_text":"-\"M**\nthatdtssssitGkb\ntc\n_LtHEE\nDER MAX COMES BACK\u2014The Teutonic slugger. Max Schmeling, is shown here being\nawarded a technical knockout over Harry Thomas last night at Madison Square Garden.\nDer Schlager, idle since he knocked out Joe Louis almost a year and a half ago, went\nagainst Thomas last night in the first of a series of warm-up tilts against popovers, in\npreparation for his return shot at Louis for the championship of the world. He banged\nThomas to the canvas seven times before Referee Arthur Donovan stopped the fight.\n\"I\n\u2014News-Acme\nJUST TO REASSURE YOU that the District is several inches south of the Mason-Dixon\nLine, we offer this blood-congealing photo of the Great Lakes tanker Regent, forced back\nto Cleveland by a winter gale after clearing that port for Toledo. The load of ice\nsigned itself on as supercargo.\nY\nEFFECT OF THE BUSINESS RECESSION on women will\nbe traced by Raymond Gram Swing, author and radio\ncommentator, at a biennial conference banquet of the Na\ntional Woman\u2019s Party at the Carlton tonight, and Vera\nBrittain (right), English author and feminist, will speak\non the topic, \u201cWomen in Transition.\u201d\nSen. Edward R.\nBurke of Nebraska also is on the program.\n\u2014News-Acme\nA TWO-MONTH-OLD TRAVELER is aboard the liner\nWesternland on a solo voyage from New York to Comines,\nBelgium, where the motherless son of Paul Duthoy is seen\nin the arms of Stewardess Sofia Knoess, who is playing\nparent to him on the high seas. The baby\u2019s father lost\nhis job soon after the mother\u2019s death.\nW\n3s\n39\n\u2014News-Acme\nTHE BLACK LEGION has disintegrated to a nightmare\nmemory in the public mind, but the law has not forgotten\nand 64-year-old Virgil II. Effinger, alleged head of the\nhooded order, is fighting extradition from Lima, O., to\nMichigan where he is wanted on criminal syndicalism\ncharges. He is shown with his 16-year-old daughter, Betty,\nas he heard a judge deny him a habeas corpus writ, but\nhe cheered up immediately when the court granted a stay\nof execution of the extradition order.\n\u2022rptr*\"OTTPWPWYPPP0P74\nT\nAA3\n\u201d\u201499\n-News-Acme\nFOUR MEN WERE KILLED and two members of the crews seriously injured when these\ntwo freight trains collided head-on near Lawrenceburg, Ky.","height":"21136","width":"14500"}}
